TITLE: Styling Dialog Component with CSS Modules
DESCRIPTION: This CSS module defines styles for the Dialog component. It includes styles for the overlay, content, title, and close button. The styles use CSS variables for customization and provide a responsive layout.
SOURCE: https://github.com/webstudio-is/webstudio-community.git/blob/main/docs/university/radix/dialog.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: CSS
CODE:
```
.overlay {
  background-color: var(--overlay-background-color);
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  animation: overlayShow 150ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
}

.content {
  background-color: var(--dialog-background-color);
  border-radius: var(--dialog-border-radius);
  box-shadow: var(--dialog-box-shadow);
  position: fixed;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  width: 90vw;
  max-width: 500px;
  max-height: 85vh;
  padding: var(--dialog-content-padding);
  animation: contentShow 150ms cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
}

.content:focus {
  outline: none;
}

.title {
  margin: 0;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--dialog-title-color);
  font-size: 17px;
}

.closeButton {
  font-family: inherit;
  border-radius: 100%;
  height: 25px;
  width: 25px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  color: var(--dialog-close-button-color);
  position: absolute;
  top: 10px;
  right: 10px;
}

.closeButton:hover {
  background-color: var(--dialog-close-button-hover-color);
}

.closeButton:focus {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--dialog-close-button-focus-ring-color);
}

@keyframes overlayShow {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
  }
}

@keyframes contentShow {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translate(-50%, -48%) scale(0.96);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1);
  }
}
```

